title: Audi AI Model
description: Model 2019, Audi has revealed its AI:Trail concept car - an all-wheel drive with drones for headlights and other features to enhance the passengers enjoyment of the outdoors. The concept vehicle, displayed at last weeks Frankfurt Motor Show, showcases what Audi sees as the future of off-road driving

title: Audi Q5
description: Model 2019, The Audi Q5 is a series of Compact luxury crossover SUVs produced by the German luxury car manufacturer Audi from 2008.[1] The original first-generation (Typ 8R) model was the third member of the B8 family to be released after the Audi A5 and fourth-generation A4, all being based on the Audi MLB platform.

title: Audi R8
description: Model 2019, The Audi R8[2] is a mid-engine, 2-seater sports car,[2][3] which uses Audis trademark quattro permanent all-wheel drive system.[2] It was introduced by the German car manufacturer Audi AG in 2006

title: Audi Etron
description: Model 2020, Audi presents the first fully electric production vehicle - the Audi e-tron. This turns Audis well-known e-tron technology into a series. Personal space, a powerful driving experience and self-determined mobility: no contradiction with the all-electric SUV from Audi. No matter whether you are travelling in the city or heading off to go sailing with friends - the Audi e-tron is suitable for everyday use and a faithful companion.
